diff:1538509277:1538487514:=1197,1199c1197,1200%0a%3c :Parentage: The Mysterium or Obrimos%0a%3c *Background presented on pg. 166 of Mysterium 1e.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Parentage: Obrimos or Mysterium%0a> %0a> *Background presented on pg. 166 of Mysterium 1e%0a> %0a1202a1204%0a> %0a1205d1206%0a%3c %0a1212d1212%0a%3c %0a1217,1223c1217,1220%0a%3c *The most basic skill of a Seeker is to see past the Lie and the deceptions around them. If the Seeker cannot pierce the deceptions around them they will never learn the hidden secrets of the world. After an instant action the Seeker is able to detect any mundane deception as the lie that it is, whereas mystically reinforced deceptions trigger a clash of wills. (As per Prime 1 Pierce Deception)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Optional Arcana: Spirit 1%0a%3c %0a%3c *Seekers also truck with spirits in pursuit of the mysteries and these entities have secrets all their own. The first trick Seekers who work in the Shadow learn is discovering the secrets of the denizens there. After an Instant Action the Seeker can discover information from a Spirit whose withstand is overcome. (As per Spirit 1 Know Spirit)%0a%3c %0a---%0a> * The most basic skill of a Seeker is to see past the Lie and the deceptions around them. If the Seeker cannot pierce the deceptions around them they will never learn the hidden secrets of the world. After an instant action the Seeker is able to detect any mundane deception as the lie that it is, whereas mystically reinforced deceptions trigger a clash of wills. (As per Prime 1 Pierce Deception)%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 1) Seekers also truck with spirits in pursuit of the mysteries and these entities have secrets all their own. The first trick seekers who work in the Shadow learn is discovering the secrets of the denizens of the Shadow. After an Instant Action the Seeker can discover information from a Spirit whose rank is less than the Seeker’s dots in the Spirit Arcanum. (As per Spirit 1 Know Spirit)%0a> %0a> %0a1226,1234c1223,1226%0a%3c *A Seeker must be able to defend themselves against other Supernal threats in order to safely indulge in their studies and explorations. Apprentices of Prime already possess the ability to counterspell Supernal magicks but the Seekers take this skill a step further by focusing their studies on self defense. Rather than gaining a new attainment, the Seekers improve their mastery of Universal Counterspell. Before rolling the clash of wills the Seeker may opt instead for automatic successes on the clash equal to their dots in Prime rather than rolling for clash.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Optional Arcana: Spirit 2%0a%3c %0a%3c *Knowing a spirit’s bane does the Seeker little good if they cannot exploit the weakness. With an instant action they may prevent a Spirit whose withstand is overcome from coming near their bane without spending willpower and the spirit may not even touch its bane willingly. This effect is transitory and as such the Seeker is well advised to use the time the spirit is held at bay wisely. (As per Invoke Bane with 1 reach to change primary factor to Potency and 1 reach for instant cast)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!Third Attainment: Seeker’s Eye%0a---%0a> * A Seeker must be able to defend themselves against other Supernal threats in order to safely indulge in their studies and explorations. Apprentices of Prime already possess the ability to counterspell Supernal magicks but the Seekers take this skill a step further by focusing their studies on self defense. Rather than gaining a new attainment, the Seekers improve their mastery of Universal Counterspell. Before rolling the clash of wills the Seeker may score automatic successes on the clash roll equal to their dots in Prime.%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 2) Seekers that travel in the Shadow must frequently defend themselves from threats that do not have a Supernal nature. Towards this end they learn to combat ephemeral threats just as they do Supernal magicks. The Seeker may now counter Spirit powers (such as Numina, Gifts, and other relevant abilities) as they would Supernal magic. When clashing against non-Supernal Spirit powers the Seeker always rolls their Gnosis+Spirit.%0a> %0a> !!!!!Third Attainment: Seeker's Eye%0a1236,1243c1228,1230%0a%3c *Seekers pride themselves on their abilities to uncover hidden secrets whether they are delving into a lost tomb or studying a recovered artifact in the safety of their Sanctum. After an instant action the Seeker may ask a number of questions regarding a subject equal to their Dots in Prime at any time during the scene. If they run out of questions they must once again take an instant action to renew their focus and continue asking questions. (As per Prime 1 Supernal Vision with 1 reach for Instant Cast, 1 reach for studying non-Supernal phenomena, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Optional Arcana: Spirit 3%0a%3c %0a%3c *The Seeker pierces the Gauntlet to investigate the world on the other side before making a dangerous journey across. This attainment may be used from either side of the Gauntlet but is withstood by Gauntlet strength as per usual. After an instant action, if the Gauntlet strength is overcome the Seeker may see across the Gauntlet for the duration of the scene. (As per Spirit 1 Exorcist’s Eye with 1 reach for instant cast, 1 reach for piercing the Gauntlet, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> * Seekers pride themselves on their abilities to uncover hidden secrets whether they are delving into a lost tomb or studying a recovered artifact in the safety of their Sanctum. After an instant action the Seeker may ask a number of questions regarding a subject equal to their Dots in Prime at any time during the scene. If they run out of questions they must once again take an instant action to renew their focus and continue asking questions. (As per Prime 1 Supernal Vision with 1 reach for Instant Cast, 1 reach for studying non-Supernal phenomena, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 3) The Seeker pierces the Gauntlet to investigate the world on the other side before making a dangerous journey across. This attainment may be used from either side of the Gauntlet but is withstood by Gauntlet strength as per usual. After an instant action, if the Gauntlet strength is overcome the Seeker may see across the Gauntlet for the duration of the scene. (As per Spirit 1 Exorcist’s Eye with 1 reach for instant cast, 1 reach for piercing the Gauntlet, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a> %0a1246,1253c1233,1236%0a%3c *Seekers explore dangerous supernal realms that can lash out at them in a moment’s notice. However, in attempting to disarm hostile magic they must also be careful not to destroy the very effects they seek to study. With an instant action the Seeker may spend a mana to selectively dispel Supernal effects near them. (As per Dispel Magic with 1 reach for instant cast, 2 reaches for lasting, 1 reach for selective targeting)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Optional Arcana: Spirit 4%0a%3c %0a%3c *Not all spirits are able to be bargained with and so a Seeker must be prepared to defend themselves against hostile attacks. By spending an instant action in preparation the Seeker may ward themselves or another being they are touching against hostile attacks from spirits and even other spiritual attacks such as Werewolf gifts. Such attacks against them first provoke a Clash of Wills before they may proceed. (As per Ephemeral Shield with 1 reach for advanced duration, 1 reach for instant cast, and 1 reach to protect against spirits’ physical attacks)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a---%0a> *Seekers explore dangerous supernal realms that can lash out at them in a moment’s notice. By maintaining vigilance they ensure that they are never caught off guard when mystical threats strike at them. This attainment further modifies Universal Counterspell and Seeker’s ward, enabling the Seeker to spend a point of willpower in order to reflexively counterspell supernal magic. Otherwise the counterspell follows the guidelines set out in the previous attainments.%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 4) Seekers who delve into the deep places of the Shadow face as much, if not more, danger than those that explore ancient Atlantean ruins or Supernal verges. The Seeker may apply Seeker’s Aegis to enhance their efforts to counter Spirit powers as laid out in Seeker’s Ward.%0a> %0a> %0a1256,1260c1239,1241%0a%3c *Finally, the Seeker learns to wash away Supernal magic with a simple wave of their hand or a mere glance. With an instant action the Seeker may suppress any Supernal effect for up to a week unless the attainment is successfully withstood. (As per Prime 4 Supernal Dispellation with 1 reach used for Instant Cast and 1 reach used for advanced Duration)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Optional Arcana: Spirit 5%0a%3c *The Seeker knows that some threats require assistance and learns to call out for aid. With an instant action the Seeker may call out to a spirit that they personally know, the closest spirit of a specific resonance, or simply the closest spirit in sensory range. The spirit arrives if it is able but is under no compulsion to obey the Seeker. Instead, the Seeker must treat with it or use further magic to compel it to act. (As per Spirit 3 Spirit Summons with 1 reach to change the primary factor to potency, 1 reach for advance duration, 1 reach for instant cast)%0a---%0a> *Finally, the Seeker learns to wash away Supernal magic with a simple wave of their hand or a mere glance. With an instant action the Seeker may suppress any Supernal effect for up to a week unless the attainment is successfully withstood. (As per Prime 4 Supernal Dispellation with 1 reach used for Instant Cast, 1 reach used for advanced Duration, and the Exceptional Success used from 5 successes used to increase the Primary Factor [Potency] by 1)%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 5) The Seeker knows that some threats require assistance and learns to call out for aid. With a ritual casting action the Seeker may call out to a spirit that they personally know, the closest spirit of a specific resonance, or simply the closest spirit in sensory range. The spirit arrives and the Seeker may give it a single complex command consisting of no more than two sentences. This binds the spirit to a task for no longer than a week unless successfully withstood. (As per Spirit 3 Spirit Summons with 1 reach to change the primary factor to potency, 2 reaches to issues a complex command, and the Exceptional Success used from 5 successes used to increase the Primary Factor [Potency] by 1)%0a> %0a
