diff:1538458491:1538458285:=1177a1178%0a> %0a1193,1194c1194,1195%0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Eyes of Ain Soph''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> !!!%25center%25''Katsinam Suukya ''%0a> %0a1197,1200c1198,1201%0a%3c :Parentage: Obrimos or Mysterium%0a%3c %0a%3c *Background presented on pg. 166 of Mysterium 1e%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Parentage: Thyrsus%0a> %0a> (Background and History are as presented in Summoners, page 195-197)%0a> %0a1203,1206c1204,1207%0a%3c :Prerequisites: Prime 2, Investigation 2, Occult 2%0a%3c %0a%3c *Most Seekers will only induct a new member if they have solved a supernatural mystery that involved significant puzzle work and investigation rather than simple brute force.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Prerequisites: Gnosis 2, Spirit 1 , Occult 2%0a> %0a> (Initiation as per Mage 1e)%0a> %0a1209,1212c1210,1213%0a%3c :Ruling Arcana: Prime%0a%3c :Yantras: Tracing Supernal runes over an object to be investigated (+2), Employing a prismatic lense(+1), Communing with Spirits (+2)%0a%3c :Oblations: Studying a mystical artifact; Investigating a Mystery whether physical or mystical; Preparing defensive wards%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Ruling Arcana: Spirit%0a> :Yantras: As this Legacy notes the melding of the old with the new, most of the Yantras that are used by them have a very old religious feel to them. They tend to be more apt to ritually cast, using sigils and circles that can take some time to prepare. Ritual Circle (+2): Whether salt, sulfer or chalk, a circle denotes the eternal continuation of cycles, the old becoming the new, and vice versa. Any power using a ritual circle ends if the circle is broken, or the caster steps outside of it.%0a> :Oblations: Prayer to spirits or other beings, ceremonies meant to celebrate old traditions. Generally speaking done with either a roll of Wits+Occult, or Presence+Occult, depending on the styling of the ritual. Telling inspiring stories of the old ways: Presence+Expression/occult%0a> %0a1215,1266d1215%0a%3c !!!!!First Attainment: Seeker’s Insight%0a%3c :Prerequisite: Initiation%0a%3c * The most basic skill of a Seeker is to see past the Lie and the deceptions around them. If the Seeker cannot pierce the deceptions around them they will never learn the hidden secrets of the world. After an instant action the Seeker is able to detect any mundane deception as the lie that it is, whereas mystically reinforced deceptions trigger a clash of wills. (As per Prime 1 Pierce Deception)%0a%3c * (Optional: Spirit 1) Seekers also truck with spirits in pursuit of the mysteries and these entities have secrets all their own. The first trick seekers who work in the Shadow learn is discovering the secrets of the denizens of the Shadow. After an Instant Action the Seeker can discover information from a Spirit whose rank is less than the Seeker’s dots in the Spirit Arcanum. (As per Spirit 1 Know Spirit)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!Second Attainment: Seeker’s Ward%0a%3c :Prerequisite: Prime 2%0a%3c * A Seeker must be able to defend themselves against other Supernal threats in order to safely indulge in their studies and explorations. Apprentices of Prime already possess the ability to counterspell Supernal magicks but the Seekers take this skill a step further by focusing their studies on self defense. Rather than gaining a new attainment, the Seekers improve their mastery of Universal Counterspell. Before rolling the clash of wills the Seeker may score automatic successes on the clash roll equal to their dots in Prime.%0a%3c * (Optional: Spirit 2) Seekers that travel in the Shadow must frequently defend themselves from threats that do not have a Supernal nature. Towards this end they learn to combat ephemeral threats just as they do Supernal magicks. The Seeker may now counter Spirit powers (such as Numina, Gifts, and other relevant abilities) as they would Supernal magic. When clashing against non-Supernal Spirit powers the Seeker always rolls their Gnosis+Spirit.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!Third Attainment: Seeker's Eye%0a%3c :Prerequisite: Prime 3%0a%3c * Seekers pride themselves on their abilities to uncover hidden secrets whether they are delving into a lost tomb or studying a recovered artifact in the safety of their Sanctum. After an instant action the Seeker may ask a number of questions regarding a subject equal to their Dots in Prime at any time during the scene. If they run out of questions they must once again take an instant action to renew their focus and continue asking questions. (As per Prime 1 Supernal Vision with 1 reach for Instant Cast, 1 reach for studying non-Supernal phenomena, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a%3c * (Optional: Spirit 3) The Seeker pierces the Gauntlet to investigate the world on the other side before making a dangerous journey across. This attainment may be used from either side of the Gauntlet but is withstood by Gauntlet strength as per usual. After an instant action, if the Gauntlet strength is overcome the Seeker may see across the Gauntlet for the duration of the scene. (As per Spirit 1 Exorcist’s Eye with 1 reach for instant cast, 1 reach for piercing the Gauntlet, and 1 reach for advanced Duration)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!Fourth Attainment: Seeker’s Aegis%0a%3c :Prerequisite: Prime 4%0a%3c *Seekers explore dangerous supernal realms that can lash out at them in a moment’s notice. By maintaining vigilance they ensure that they are never caught off guard when mystical threats strike at them. This attainment further modifies Universal Counterspell and Seeker’s ward, enabling the Seeker to spend a point of willpower in order to reflexively counterspell supernal magic. Otherwise the counterspell follows the guidelines set out in the previous attainments.%0a%3c * (Optional: Spirit 4) Seekers who delve into the deep places of the Shadow face as much, if not more, danger than those that explore ancient Atlantean ruins or Supernal verges. The Seeker may apply Seeker’s Aegis to enhance their efforts to counter Spirit powers as laid out in Seeker’s Ward.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!Fifth Attainment: Seeker's Mastery%0a%3c :Prerequisite: Prime 5%0a%3c *Finally, the Seeker learns to wash away Supernal magic with a simple wave of their hand or a mere glance. With an instant action the Seeker may suppress any Supernal effect for up to a week unless the attainment is successfully withstood. (As per Prime 4 Supernal Dispellation with 1 reach used for Instant Cast, 1 reach used for advanced Duration, and the Exceptional Success used from 5 successes used to increase the Primary Factor [Potency] by 1)%0a%3c * (Optional: Spirit 5) The Seeker knows that some threats require assistance and learns to call out for aid. With a ritual casting action the Seeker may call out to a spirit that they personally know, the closest spirit of a specific resonance, or simply the closest spirit in sensory range. The spirit arrives and the Seeker may give it a single complex command consisting of no more than two sentences. This binds the spirit to a task for no longer than a week unless successfully withstood. (As per Spirit 3 Spirit Summons with 1 reach to change the primary factor to potency, 2 reaches to issues a complex command, and the Exceptional Success used from 5 successes used to increase the Primary Factor [Potency] by 1)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25''Katsinam Suukya ''%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!Origins%0a%3c %0a%3c :Parentage: Thyrsus%0a%3c %0a%3c (Background and History are as presented in Summoners, page 195-197)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!Doctrine%0a%3c %0a%3c :Prerequisites: Gnosis 2, Spirit 1 , Occult 2%0a%3c %0a%3c (Initiation as per Mage 1e)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!Magic%0a%3c %0a%3c :Ruling Arcana: Spirit%0a%3c :Yantras: As this Legacy notes the melding of the old with the new, most of the Yantras that are used by them have a very old religious feel to them. They tend to be more apt to ritually cast, using sigils and circles that can take some time to prepare. Ritual Circle (+2): Whether salt, sulfer or chalk, a circle denotes the eternal continuation of cycles, the old becoming the new, and vice versa. Any power using a ritual circle ends if the circle is broken, or the caster steps outside of it.%0a%3c :Oblations: Prayer to spirits or other beings, ceremonies meant to celebrate old traditions. Generally speaking done with either a roll of Wits+Occult, or Presence+Occult, depending on the styling of the ritual. Telling inspiring stories of the old ways: Presence+Expression/occult%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!Attainments%0a%3c %0a1654a1604,1655%0a> %0a> %0a> %25right%25[[#top|&#8593; back to top]]%0a> %0a> !!!%25center%25''Eyes of Ain Soph''%0a> %0a> !!!!Origins%0a> %0a> :Parentage: Obrimos or Mysterium%0a> %0a> *Background presented on pg. 166 of Mysterium 1e%0a> %0a> !!!!Doctrine%0a> %0a> :Prerequisites: Prime 2, Investigation 2, Occult 2%0a> %0a> *Most Seekers will only induct a new member if they have solved a supernatural mystery that involved significant puzzle work and investigation rather than simple brute force.%0a> %0a> !!!!Magic%0a> %0a> :Ruling Arcana: Prime%0a> :Yantras: Tracing Supernal runes over an object to be investigated (+2), Employing a prismatic lense(+1), Communing with Spirits (+2)%0a> :Oblations: Studying a mystical artifact; Investigating a Mystery whether physical or mystical; Preparing defensive wards%0a> %0a> !!!!Attainments%0a> %0a> !!!!!First Attainment: Seeker’s Insight%0a> :Prerequisite: Initiation%0a> * The most basic skill of a Seeker is to see past the Lie and the deceptions around them. If the Seeker cannot pierce the deceptions around them they will never learn the hidden secrets of the world. After an instant action the Seeker is able to detect any mundane deception as the lie that it is, whereas mystically reinforced deceptions trigger a clash of wills. (As per Prime 1 Pierce Deception)%0a> * (Optional: Spirit 1) Seekers also truck with spirits in pursuit of the mysteries and these entities have secrets all their own. The first trick seekers who