diff:1535956492:1535956054:minor=430,431c430,431%0a%3c *Note that substances created directly from Kindred Vitae have no ability to sustain life properly; water is oddly foul, food rotted, and air borderline toxic. However, it’s rumored that Elder Geheim are unique among sorcery practitioners in that they may have an ability that allows their Formulae to bypass this limitation with a form of ‘purification’. This will similarly allow valuable materials to be created properly with rituals like Vitae Transmutation. (Mechanically, to do this, an Elder Geheim casts a ritual with twice the cost and twice the successes needed)%0a%3c %0a---%0a> *Note that substances created directly from Kindred Vitae have no ability to sustain life properly; water is oddly foul, food rotted, and air borderline toxic. However, it’s rumored that Elder Geheim are unique among sorcery practitioners in that they may have an ability that allows their Formulae to bypass this limitation with a form of ‘purification’. This will similarly allow valuable materials to be created properly with rituals like Vitae Transmutation.%0a> %0a498a499,500%0a> **“Valuable” materials created with this ritual are inherently flawed and useless for the sake of monetary purposes, but suffice fine for anything needed for mystical equipment and similar purposes that don’t directly rely on Availability.%0a> %0a513a516,517%0a> *As with the base ritual, the Blut Alchemie rating and Potency limit the equipment created, but it no longer needs to be anything homogenous. Valuable materials are still too flawed to be of any actual material use.%0a> %0a790c794%0a%3c !!!!!Coil of The Void%0a---%0a> !!!Coil of The Void%0a793,794c797%0a%3c :Scent of the Unknown •:%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Scent of the Unknown: •%0a801,802c804,805%0a%3c :Taste of the Forbidden ••:%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Taste of the Forbidden: ••%0a> %0a810,812c813,816%0a%3c :Strength of the Arcane •••:%0a%3c While most Kindred are limited in the Potency of their Blood and their knowledge of Disciplines when it comes to the sheer ‘presence’ of their powers, the Renatus learn to channel supernatural force from elsewhere to bolster themselves further, becoming sensitive to their own abilities in the process.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Strength of the Arcane: •••%0a> While most Kindred are limited in th%0a> e Potency of their Blood and their knowledge of Disciplines when it comes to the sheer ‘presence’ of their powers, the Renatus learn to channel supernatural force from elsewhere to bolster themselves further, becoming sensitive to their own abilities in the process.%0a> %0a818,819c822,823%0a%3c :Aura of the Otherworld ••••:%0a%3c %0a---%0a> :Aura of the Otherworld: ••••%0a> %0a824,836c828,839%0a%3c ->'''Depleted'''%0a%3c %0a%3c ->Your character’s supernatural energy has been drained away, causing an unnatural need to fill the void created. Any activation of a supernatural ability or related Clash of Wills suffers a -2 penalty, and the Kindred who inflicted this on you gets an exceptional success on three instead of fives successes for any rolls to utilize or Clash with a power of their own on you, as your pattern invites the supernatural energy inside more willingly. As well, any such exceptional success allows them to drain a point of Energy from your character, if you use an energy source other than Vitae (gaining it as Umbral Energy in the process). %0a%3c %0a%3c ->This Condition fades naturally after a number of nights equal to the Blood Potency of the vampire who caused it. %0a%3c %0a%3c ->Possible Sources: Aura of the Otherworld.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->Resolution: Regain at least 5 points of supernatural energy in one scene. Face a breaking point due to a use of a supernatural power (by or against you). %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c :Soul of The Void •••••:%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Depleted%0a> %0a> Your character’s supernatural energy has been drained away, causing an unnatural need to fill the void created. Any activation of a supernatural ability or related Clash