diff:1535325487:1535324524:=393,394c393,394%0a%3c Unreliant on the tenants of Humanity, Blut Alchemie is not limited by it; instead, performing it requires access to a Laboratory, generally requiring complexity needing a Safe Place or Nest of a rating at least equal to the rating of the ritual (''which they call Formulae'') to be performed. Alternatively, they can ‘make due’ with a less secure mundane lab with an equipment bonus at least equal to the level of the ritual, but they take a -2 penalty to tactuallyoll (''which does not actual gain the lab’s equipment bonus'') due to the unspecialized tools they’re working with. %0a%3c %0a---%0a> Unreliant on the tenants of Humanity, Blut Alchemie is not limited by it; instead, performing it requires access to a Laboratory, generally requiring complexity needing a Safe Place or Nest of a rating at least equal to the rating of the ritual (''which they call Formulae'') to be performed. Alternatively, they can ‘make due’ with a less secure mundane lab with an equipment bonus at least equal to the level of the ritual, but they take a -2 penalty to tactuallyoll (which does not actual gain the lab’s equipment bonus) due to the unspecialized tools they’re working with. %0a> %0a397,407c397,408%0a%3c :Dice Pool: Intelligence + Science + Blut Alchemie%0a%3c *On an exceptional success, they have the option of taking the Informed (''Vitae'') condition, and on a dramatic failure they take the Confused condition.%0a%3c :Cost: Vitae equal to the ritual level, or pints of ‘donor’ blood equal to twice the ritual level.%0a%3c *Note that substances created directly from Kindred Vitae have no ability to sustain life properly; water is oddly foul, food rotted, and air borderline toxic. However, it’s rumored that Elder Geheim are unique among sorcery practitioners in that they may have an ability that allows their Formulae to bypass this limitation with a form of ‘purification’. This will similarly allow valuable materials to be created properly with rituals like Vitae Transmutation.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!%25center%25'''Blut Alchemie Formulae'''%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Sanguine Analysis''' (•)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 2%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Dice Pool: Intelligence + Science + Blut Alchemie\%0a> On an exceptional success, they have the option of taking the Informed (Vitae) condition, and on a dramatic failure they take the Confused condition.\%0a> Cost: Vitae equal to the ritual level, or pints of ‘donor’ blood equal to twice the ritual level.\%0a> %0a> Note that substances created directly from Kindred Vitae have no ability to sustain life properly; water is oddly foul, food rotted, and air borderline toxic. However, it’s rumored that Elder Geheim are unique among sorcery practitioners in that they may have an ability that allows their Formulae to bypass this limitation with a form of ‘purification’. This will similarly allow valuable materials to be created properly with rituals like Vitae Transmutation.%0a> %0a> Blut Alchemie Formulae%0a> %0a> Sanguine Analysis (•)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 2%0a> %0a409,421c410,424%0a%3c *Any information that could be garnered with a Taste of Blood success.%0a%3c *Any information that could be garnered with a Taste of Blood exceptional success.%0a%3c *The amount of blood that was in a subject’s system at the time the sample was taken.%0a%3c *The age of the character (''if mortal'') or time since the character’s Embrace or last torpor, whichever was most recent (''if Kindred'').%0a%3c *Whether the subject is blood bound to someone (''if so, another point of Potency can discern who if you’ve studied a sample of their blood before'')%0a%3c *The clan of a ghoul’s regnant, the bloodline of a Kindred, the ‘subdivision’ of a type of supernatural (''such as a Werewolf’s Auspice''), or a similar ‘detailed’ bit of information about a creature’s type, to the extent the Geheim knows to categorize them (''otherwise he simply knows sample X and Y are different'').%0a%3c **An advanced version of this ritual exists, at 3 dots, that allows the player to ask the above or other relevant questions per point of Potency, rather than receiving the information in ‘order’. %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Vitae Distillation''' (•)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 4 + target%0a%3c *Through strange procedures involving the alteration of the Kindred’s own Vitae (''or an appropriately processed sample from elsewhere''), the Vampire becomes able to ‘create’ liquids from it with this formulae. %0a%3c %0a---%0a> •	Any information that could be garnered with a Taste of Blood success.%0a> •	Any information that could be garnered with a Taste of Blood exceptional success.%0a> •	The amount of blood that was in a subject’s system at the time the sample%0a> was taken.%0a> •	The age of the character (if mortal) or time since the character’s Embrace or last torpor, whichever was most recent (if Kindred).%0a> •	Whether the subject is blood bound to someone (if so, another point of Potency can discern who if you’ve studied a sample of their blood before)%0a> •	The clan of a ghoul’s regnant, the bloodline of a Kindred, the ‘subdivision’ of a type of supernatural (such as a Werewolf’s Auspice), or a similar ‘detailed’ bit of information about a creature’s type, to the extent the Geheim knows to categorize them (otherwise he simply knows sample X and Y are different).%0a> An advanced version of this ritual exists, at 3 dots, that allows the player to ask the above or other relevant questions per point of Potency, rather than receiving the information in ‘order’. %0a> %0a> Vitae Distillation (•)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 4 + target%0a> %0a> Through strange procedures involving the alteration of the Kindred’s own Vitae (or an appropriately processed sample from elsewhere), the Vampire becomes able to ‘create’ liquids from it with this formulae. %0a> %0a430,438c433,441%0a%3c *In the case of an appropriate equipment bonus or Toxicity (''such as for a poisonous substance''), the amount is equal to the Potency of the ritual. Damage ratings of unstable substances are capped at the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating, as well, and any failure on a formulae roll creating such a substance causes it to immediately ‘go off’, with appropriately disastrous results.%0a%3c %0a%3c Substances thus created break down after about a Month, unless upheld by a Dilettante’s Laboratory (''see the merit below''). %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Vitae Sublimation''' (••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 5 + target%0a%3c *An extension of Vitae Distillation, which most Geheim will always learn first, this more complex ritual allows the Kindred to transform their blood into gaseous states. Obviously, doing so without proper containment is of limited usefulness. %0a%3c %0a---%0a> In the case of an appropriate equipment bonus or Toxicity (such as for a poisonous substance), the amount is equal to the Potency of the ritual. Damage ratings of unstable substances are capped at the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating, as well, and any failure on a formulae roll creating such a substance causes it to immediately ‘go off’, with appropriately disastrous results.%0a> %0a> Substances thus created break down after about a Month, unless upheld by a Dilettante’s Laboratory (see the merit below). %0a> %0a> Vitae Sublimation (••)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 5 + target%0a> An extension of Vitae Distillation, which most Geheim will always learn first, this more complex ritual allows the Kindred to transform their blood into gaseous states. Obviously, doing so without proper containment is of limited usefulness. %0a> %0a448,457c451,460%0a%3c *In the case of an appropriate equipment bonus or Toxicity (''such as for a poisonous substance''), the amount is equal to the Potency of the ritual. Damage ratings of unstable substances are capped at the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating, as well, and any failure on a formulae roll creating such a substance causes it to immediately ‘go off’, with appropriately disastrous results.%0a%3c %0a%3c Substances thus created break down after about a Month, unless upheld by a Dilettante’s Laboratory (''see the merit below''). %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Vitae Transmutation''' (•••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 6 + target%0a%3c %0a%3c *A further application of Vitae Sublimation, the Kindred becomes capable of creating homogeneous solid substances from their blood (which can be shaped into appropriate equipment in the process). %0a%3c %0a---%0a> In the case of an appropriate equipment bonus or Toxicity (such as for a poisonous substance), the amount is equal to the Potency of the ritual. Damage ratings of unstable substances are capped at the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating, as well, and any failure on a formulae roll creating such a substance causes it to immediately ‘go off’, with appropriately disastrous results.%0a> %0a> Substances thus created break down after about a Month, unless upheld by a Dilettante’s Laboratory (see the merit below). %0a> %0a> Vitae Transmutation (•••)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 6 + target%0a> %0a> A further application of Vitae Sublimation, the Kindred becomes capable of creating homogeneous solid substances from their blood (which can be shaped into appropriate equipment in the process). %0a> %0a467,475c470,478%0a%3c *This can be made into any simple (''read: non mechanical or electronic'') equipment as part of the creation process, so long as it’s made out of a single substance (''homogeneous mixtures, alloys, and similar count towards this, it doesn’t need to be a single molecule, just recognizable as ‘one thing’''), with a bonus, damage, or other equipment value total equal to the lesser of the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating and the formulae’s Potency.%0a%3c %0a%3c **“Valuable” materials created with this ritual are inherently flawed and useless for the sake of monetary purposes, but suffice fine for anything needed for mystical equipment and similar purposes that don’t directly rely on Availability.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Advanced Vitae Transmutation''' (••••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 7 + target%0a%3c *By further refining and altering studied blood, the Kindred can create complex substances and equipment beyond what can be done with the lesser version of this ritual. %0a%3c %0a---%0a> This can be made into any simple (read: non mechanical or electronic) equipment as part of the creation process, so long as it’s made out of a single substance (homogeneous mixtures, alloys, and similar count towards this, it doesn’t need to be a single molecule, just recognizable as ‘one thing’), with a bonus, damage, or other equipment value total equal to the lesser of the practitioner’s Blut Alchemie rating and the formulae’s Potency.%0a> %0a> “Valuable” materials created with this ritual are inherently flawed and useless for the sake of monetary purposes, but suffice fine for anything needed for mystical equipment and similar purposes that don’t directly rely on Availability.%0a> %0a> Advanced Vitae Transmutation (••••)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 7 + target%0a> By further refining and altering studied blood, the Kindred can create complex substances and equipment beyond what can be done with the lesser version of this ritual. %0a> %0a486,519c489,521%0a%3c *As with the base ritual, the Blut Alchemie rating and Potency limit the equipment created, but it no longer needs to be anything homogenous. Valuable materials are still too flawed to be of any actual material use.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Internal Athanor''' (•••••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Number of Successes: 12%0a%3c %0a%3c :Contested by: Stamina + Blood Potency, '''if target unwilling'''%0a%3c %0a%3c By specially preparing and then consuming the blood utilized in this Formulae (''which must be Vitae in this case''), the Kindred subject becomes capable of unlocking the potential held within a given Kindred’s blood. The substance created needn’t be consumed immediately, but goes inert at the end of the night, whether consumed or not.%0a%3c Once it is consumed, the Kindred (''which can be the Gheim themself'') who’s consumed it has their effective Blood Potency increased by an amount equal to the ritual’s Potency, capped by the Geheim’s rating in Blut Alchemie. This applies to all dice pools, derived traits, Banes, and other effects, except for anything lasting, such as the result of being Diablerized. However, the predatory aura, supernatural tolerance, clash of wills, kindred senses, frenzy bonuses, sunlight damage, feeding restrictions, and anything similar are all affected. The bonus fades on the next sunrise. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''Bloody Bezoar''' (•••••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Target Successes: 14+Extra Potency%0a%3c *This complicated ritual creates a sanguine stone capable of curing the few remedies and maladies capable of harming Kindred. To start with, the Kindred must break down the blood used in its sacrifice, which '''MUST''' be Vitae in this case, into a special substance, which is then fed to a non-human Mammal of some sort. Over the course of the ritual’s casting, the animal becomes poisoned and dies a fairly painful death, at the end of which its stomach may be cut open to retrieve the stone inside. The Kindred may purposely raise the target number to add the additional successes to the stone’s Potency, in addition to the usual means of determining a formulae’s Potency.%0a%3c %0a%3c *After creation, the stone will last for the next month (''or longer if held by a Dilettante’s Laboratory, below''). If consumed during that time period by a Kindred or other Undead being, its curative properties immediately take effect. %0a%3c %0a%3c Its Potency is split between any or all of the following effects, as desired:%0a%3c %0a%3c *Nullification of Toxicity (''whether through disease or poison'') equal to the Potency applied; supernatural toxins likely require a Clash of Wills to defeat. If the toxicity is lowered to 0 or less, the toxin or diseased is considered entirely gone, and the Kindred may not be reinfected by the same one for the night. %0a%3c %0a%3c *Allowing Vitae to be spent (''at normal cost'') to heal a point of aggravated damage per Potency immediately, instead of needing to sleep for the night. %0a%3c %0a%3c *Curing a Physical Condition or Tilt that would require a number of Vitae equal to Potency to remove normally, or a flat 3 Potency for any other Physical Condition or Tilt.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Heal a number of Bashing damage equal to applied Potency without requiring Vitae.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!!%25center%25'''New Merit''': ''Dilettante’s Laboratory'' (• to •••••)%0a%3c %0a%3c :Prerequisites: Safe Place or Nest Guardian (''if Ordo'') at same level. Blut Alchemie •%0a%3c %0a---%0a> As with the base ritual, the Blut Alchemie rating and Potency limit the equipment created, but it no longer needs to be anything homogenous. Valuable materials are still too flawed to be of any actual material use.%0a> %0a> Internal Athanor (•••••)%0a> %0a> Target Number of Successes: 12%0a> %0a> Contested by: Stamina + Blood Potency, if target unwilling%0a> %0a> By specially preparing and then consuming the blood utilized in this Formulae (which must be Vitae in this case), the Kindred subject becomes capable of unlocking the potential held within a given Kindred’s blood. The substance created needn’t be consumed immediately, but goes inert at the end of the night, whether consumed or not.%0a> Once it is consumed, the Kindred (which can be the Gheim themself) who’s consumed it has their effective Blood Potency increased by an amount equal to the ritual’s Potency, capped by the Geheim’s rating in Blut Alchemie. This applies to all dice pools, derived traits, Banes, and other effects, except for anything lasting, such as the result of being Diablerized. However, the predatory aura, supernatural tolerance, clash of wills, kindred senses, frenzy bonuses, sunlight damage, feeding restrictions, and anything similar are all affected. The bonus fades on the next sunrise. %0a> %0a> %0a> Bloody Bezoar (•••••)%0a> %0a> Target Successes: 14+Extra Potency%0a> %0a> This complicated ritual creates a sanguine stone capable of curing the few remedies and maladies capable of harming Kindred. To start with, the Kindred must break down the blood used in its sacrifice, which MUST be Vitae in this case, into a special substance, which is then fed to a non-human Mammal of some sort. Over the course of the ritual’s casting, the animal becomes poisoned and dies a fairly painful death, at the end of which its stomach may be cut open to retrieve the stone inside. The Kindred may purposely raise the target number to add the additional successes to the stone’s Potency, in addition to the usual means of determining a formulae’s Potency.%0a> %0a> After creation, the stone will last for the next month (or longer if held by a Dilettante’s Laboratory, below). If consumed during that time period by a Kindred or other Undead being, its curative properties immediately take effect. Its Potency is split between any or all of the following effects, as desired:%0a> %0a> Nullification of Toxicity (whether through disease or poison) equal to the Potency applied; supernatural toxins likely require a Clash of Wills to defeat. If the toxicity is lowered to 0 or less, the toxin or diseased is considered entirely gone, and the Kindred may not be reinfected by the same one for the night. %0a> %0a> Allowing Vitae to be spent (at normal cost) to heal a point of aggravated damage per Potency immediately, instead of needing to sleep for the night. %0a> %0a> Curing a Physical Condition or Tilt that would require a number of Vitae equal to Potency to remove normally, or a flat 3 Potency for any other Physical Condition or Tilt.%0a> %0a> Heal a number of Bashing damage equal to applied Potency without requiring Vitae.%0a> %0a> %0a> New Merit: Dilettante’s Laboratory (• to •••••)%0a> %0a> Prerequisites: Safe Place or Nest Guardian (if Ordo) at same level. Blut Alchemie •%0a> %0a522,524c524,526%0a%3c :Effect: The Laboratory’s rating indicates its approximate size or complexity, which must be contained within an appropriately designed Safe Place or appropriately powerful Wyrm’s Nest. Its most basic ability is its allowance of highly complex ‘formulae kits’, that is, small collections of specialized tools and equipment that will allow the Geheim to perform Blut Alchemie without direct presence within the Lab, by expending the contents of such a kit. The merit’s dots indicate the total ‘rating’ of formulae that may be portably cast this way per chapter (''so a 4 dot Lab might allow a casting of a 3 dot and a 1 dot Formulae, or two 2 dots, etc'').%0a%3c %0a%3c In addition, the unique tools within make the performance of Blut Alchemie that much more reliable. When using the lab (''and the Kindred’s actually inside it''), the merit’s rating is added to any Formulae activation rolls, and a number of Formulae cast there that would last at least a scene may be ‘hung’ on the lab, being upkept indefinitely until another replaces it (''the Dilettante chooses when replacements occur, it’s not automatic''). %0a---%0a> Effect: The Laboratory’s rating indicates its approximate size or complexity, which must be contained within an appropriately designed Safe Place or appropriately powerful Wyrm’s Nest. Its most basic ability is its allowance of highly complex ‘formulae kits’, that is, small collections of specialized tools and equipment that will allow the Geheim to perform Blut Alchemie without direct presence within the Lab, by expending the contents of such a kit. The merit’s dots indicate the total ‘rating’ of formulae that may be portably cast this way per chapter (so a 4 dot Lab might allow a casting of a 3 dot and a 1 dot Formulae, or two 2 dots, etc).%0a> %0a> In addition, the unique tools within make the performance of Blut Alchemie that much more reliable. When using the lab (and the Kindred’s actually inside it), the merit’s rating is added to any Formulae activation rolls, and a number of Formulae cast there that would last at least a scene may be ‘hung’ on the lab, being upkept indefinitely until another replaces it (the Dilettante chooses when replacements occur, it’s not automatic). %0a
